			<div class="content" id="post-content-1823310">
									

<p>There are a couple of explanations for this. Out-of-universe, this is a relic from the first incarnations of the Foundation, and D-class were disposable basically as a way for showing the Foundation's utter lack of scruples in sacrificing people as a way of testing/containing SCP items. In-universe, I see it basically as internal propoganda to assuage the guilt of researchers. &quot;Yeah, that guy you're sending to his death is a multiple child rapist/murderer and was gonna be killed at the end of the month anyway. Might as well get some use out of him first.&quot;</p>

