					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/andarielhalo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1750255); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1750255&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252462" alt="AndarielHalo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1750255)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/andarielhalo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1750255); return false;" >AndarielHalo</a></span> <span class="odate time_1383327615 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Nov 2013 17:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1883171">
									

<p>In that case, they could be contained permanently, and the Foundation could have, say, 10,000-50,000 Class-D Personnel at all times, to be re-used as necessary. Or they could even requisition an entire prison for themselves, and house all their D's there. Literally anything involving a stagnant population of Class-D would be preferable to what is literally systematic genocide.</p>
<p>Not even going into the logistics of what constitutes &quot;crime&quot;- someone convicted of a murder might've been coerced into it, or taking the fall for a family member or loved one, or even falsely accused altogether. Not to mention minor crimes, or innocent mistakes, that would be considered &quot;violent&quot; in another culture that neighbors an SCP facility.</p>

							</div>

								
					
