<p>This comforts me a bit. I recognize this is all fiction and such, but the more I thought about it, the more agitated and disturbed I became, on a moral level. It seems to me that, if this system were canon, then the SCP would be more responsible for human death and suffering than any of the SCPs being (successfully) contained, and would eventually (if not already) put the Ottoman Empire and Nazi Germany to shame. Criminals or not, they're still people.</p>

